result.description:
The conclusion to Shingeki no Kyojin, also known as Attack on Titan, has left fans with mixed emotions. The highly-anticipated finale of the popular anime series has been met with both praise and criticism.

The conclusion of the story ties up loose ends and answers many questions that have been lingering throughout the series. However, some fans were left feeling unsatisfied with the resolution of certain plot points and the fates of certain characters.

Despite this, the final season of Shingeki no Kyojin has been a commercial success, with many fans eagerly awaiting the release of the final Blu-ray and DVD collections. The series has also helped to raise the profile of anime and manga globally, with its popularity continuing to grow.

Overall, the conclusion to Shingeki no Kyojin may not have been perfect, but it still managed to deliver a thrilling and memorable ending to a beloved series.
